This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) of clinical narratives, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The study also involves evaluating the performance of an NLP system, which could be considered a machine learning task and thus falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of echocardiograms suggests that computer vision (cs.CV) could also be a relevant sub-category. The study involves analyzing data from multiple medical centers, which could involve issues related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybersecurity (cs.CY).
